The authentication ip-conflict-check enable command enables the client IP address conflict detection function.
The undo authentication ip-conflict-check enable command disables the client IP address conflict detection function. The authentication ip-conflict-check enable command enables the client IP address conflict detection function. The undo authentication ip-conflict-check enable command disables the client IP address conflict detection function. By default, the device detects whether client IP addresses conflict with each other. This command is supported only on the CE6863H, CE6863H-K, CE6881H, CE6881H-K, CE6820H, CE6820H-K and CE6820S.
